arts.ttl: Preston upset Fulham in EFL-Cup record shootout
arts.sum: Championship side Preston secured the biggest shock of the Carabao Cup third round on Tuesday, beating Premier League Fulham 16-15 in the longest penalty shootout in the competition's history.

arts.ttl: Fulham lose longest penalty shootout in League Cup history as Premier League side crash out to Championship club Preston in third round after THIRTY-FOUR spot-kicks
arts.sum: AADAM PATEL AT DEEPDALE: Championship Preston North End knocked out Fulham last night after the longest penalty shoot-out in League Cup history.

arts.ttl: Paul Heckingbottom was desperate for Preston to win marathon penalty shoot-out
arts.sum: After a 1-1 draw in normal time, Timothy Castagne ballooned over and Ryan Ledson sent Steven Benda the wrong way.

arts.ttl: See it to believe it! Fulham, Preston take 34 penalties in agonising shootout!
arts.sum: Preston and Fulham set a record as they played out the longest penalty shootout in League Cup history.

arts.ttl: Match Officials Mic'd Up: Webb analyses key incidents in MW1-3
arts.sum: What the match officials did: Referee Chris Kavanagh spots that Rice kicks the ball away before Veltman catches him, he then issues Rice a second yellow card for delaying the restart of play. What the match officials did: The assistant referee says the ball strikes Kovacic but believes his arm is in a natural position and the ball comes at him at speed.

arts.ttl: Liverpool record smashed as Preston cause Premier League shock
arts.sum: Liverpool have been knocked off their perch by Preston North End after the Championship club set a new penalty shootout record. The Lilywhites entertained Premier League side Fulham in the third round of the League Cup on Tuesday night and took a surprise lead before the half through Ryan Ledson. arts.ttl: Preston win epic THIRTY-FOUR penalty shoot-out to edge Fulham

arts.ttl: Ryan Ledson holds his nerve as Preston win marathon penalty shoot-out
